WEBVTT

00:28.330 --> 00:29.880
Who can tell me
the biggest mistake

00:29.880 --> 00:31.580
people make in a crisis?

00:34.790 --> 00:35.790
Mm-hmm?

00:35.790 --> 00:37.750
A failure to plan.

00:37.750 --> 00:39.920
Crisis management
isn't about planning.

00:39.920 --> 00:42.330
It's about action.
Snap decisions in the moment.

00:42.330 --> 00:45.000
An ineffective
communication strategy.

00:45.000 --> 00:46.170
Student #3:
Telling the truth.

00:46.170 --> 00:48.420
[ Laughter ]

00:48.420 --> 00:50.460
People think
we lie for a living.

00:50.460 --> 00:51.790
But in fact,

00:51.790 --> 00:53.580
the truth is often
our greatest weapon.

00:53.580 --> 00:55.080
Anyone else?

00:58.420 --> 01:00.670
Woman: Not knowing
they're in a crisis.

01:00.670 --> 01:02.540
Very good.

01:02.540 --> 01:03.920
Miss...

01:03.920 --> 01:05.500
Keating.

01:05.500 --> 01:07.120
Annalise Keating.

01:07.120 --> 01:08.120
♪♪

01:14.580 --> 01:18.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:18.580 --> 01:19.620
Ms. Pope.

01:19.620 --> 01:22.250
Ms. Keating.

01:22.250 --> 01:24.080
That was a very informed answer
earlier.

01:24.080 --> 01:25.290
Spoken from experience?

01:25.290 --> 01:26.420
I'm a defense attorney.

01:26.420 --> 01:28.250
I taught at Middleton Law School
for years.

01:28.250 --> 01:31.170
Professor Keating...?

01:31.170 --> 01:34.040
I'm sorry.
Oh, no.

01:34.040 --> 01:35.580
I'm happy
that my own business

01:35.580 --> 01:37.790
never caught
your attention.
[ Laughs ]

01:37.790 --> 01:39.960
I'm representing
a class-action case

01:39.960 --> 01:41.460
that has the potential

01:41.460 --> 01:43.880
to reform
our entire justice system.

01:43.880 --> 01:45.880
I have
about 100 plaintiffs --

01:45.880 --> 01:47.920
all mostly poor,
people of color --

01:47.920 --> 01:49.380
who have been incarcerated

01:49.380 --> 01:51.540
due to underfunded
public defenders.

01:51.540 --> 01:53.830
The case was just shot down
by Pennsylvania courts.

01:53.830 --> 01:55.080
Mm.

01:55.080 --> 01:56.580
I wish you a lot of luck.

01:56.580 --> 01:58.250
Luck?

01:58.250 --> 01:59.500
People's
constitutional rights

01:59.500 --> 02:00.920
are being violated
every single day

02:00.920 --> 02:03.380
in every courtroom
across the country.

02:03.380 --> 02:05.210
Luck is for cereal
with marshmallows.

02:05.210 --> 02:06.540
[ Laughs ]

02:06.540 --> 02:08.290
I need your help.

02:08.290 --> 02:10.040
I'm not sure how I can.

02:10.040 --> 02:11.290
I'm not
a practicing lawyer.

02:11.290 --> 02:12.380
Annalise:
I don't need another lawyer.

02:12.380 --> 02:15.290
I need this case
to be fast-tracked

02:15.290 --> 02:17.120
to the United States
Supreme Court.

02:17.120 --> 02:20.580
Oh.

02:20.580 --> 02:21.750
I don't know
if you've heard,

02:21.750 --> 02:22.830
but I've been
out of the White House

02:22.830 --> 02:23.880
for a few months now.

02:23.880 --> 02:25.580
The news said
you left on good terms.

02:25.580 --> 02:26.790
I did.

02:26.790 --> 02:29.960
But I'm sort of enjoying
my break from politics.

02:29.960 --> 02:31.620
Who's talking politics?

02:31.620 --> 02:32.830
I'm talking justice.

02:32.830 --> 02:34.170
Ending the new Jim Crow.

02:34.170 --> 02:36.000
Here, read this case file.

02:36.000 --> 02:37.540
I --
Just look it over.

02:37.540 --> 02:39.040
You can say no then.

02:44.420 --> 02:45.830
Ms. Pope.

02:46.790 --> 02:49.920
Our country's in crisis.

02:49.920 --> 02:51.420
Together we can fix it.

02:56.330 --> 02:59.580
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

02:59.580 --> 03:02.040
Abby: I've rescheduled
Party-boy Banker for tomorrow,

03:02.040 --> 03:04.120
so today we just have
Senator Embarrassing X-Ray

03:04.120 --> 03:05.540
and the oil lobbyist

03:05.540 --> 03:06.420
with the little
money-laundering sitch.

03:06.420 --> 03:08.420
Huck: I'm also converting
all the machines

03:08.420 --> 03:10.250
to a stronger
encryption protocol.

03:10.250 --> 03:11.120
So that'll take us offline
for a few hours.

03:11.120 --> 03:12.460
You just have
to tell me when.

03:12.460 --> 03:14.710
We were thinking
maybe Friday night.

03:16.880 --> 03:18.330
Quinn.

03:18.330 --> 03:19.920
Did you hear anything
we just said?

03:19.920 --> 03:20.960
Quinn:
Uh, today is X-Ray Senator

03:20.960 --> 03:21.920
and money laundry
oil lobbyist.

03:21.920 --> 03:23.830
Tomorrow
is Party Boy Banker.

03:23.830 --> 03:25.880
Abby: Also, Charlie reached out
to a couple of PI's

03:25.880 --> 03:27.830
for extra help with all
the tails we're running.

03:27.830 --> 03:29.620
We'll want to sit down
with them.
Mm-hmm.

03:29.620 --> 03:31.580
So, maybe next week,
or...?"
Sure.

03:31.580 --> 03:32.670
Sooner would be better.

03:32.670 --> 03:33.750
Fine.

03:33.750 --> 03:34.880
Charlie can run point on that,
right?

03:34.880 --> 03:36.710
Um...probably?

03:36.710 --> 03:38.000
I'll check.

03:42.920 --> 03:44.080
I'm sorry.
Was there something else?

03:44.080 --> 03:45.580
You're Googling Liv again,
aren't you?

03:50.040 --> 03:51.580
She's teaching college.

03:51.580 --> 03:52.620
Teaching?

03:52.620 --> 03:54.290
Well,
you know what they say.

03:54.290 --> 03:55.620
Those who can't do...

03:55.620 --> 03:57.000
[ Laughs ] You're bad.

03:57.000 --> 03:59.000
Liv's worse.

03:59.000 --> 04:00.210
Good riddance.

04:00.210 --> 04:01.460
Right?

04:01.460 --> 04:03.040
Right.

04:03.040 --> 04:05.040
♪♪

04:05.040 --> 04:06.790
[ Inhales deeply,
exhales ]

04:06.790 --> 04:12.790
♪♪

04:13.080 --> 04:15.540
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

04:15.540 --> 04:16.920
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:16.920 --> 04:18.290
Marcus:
Annalise Keating.

04:18.290 --> 04:21.120
The Annalise Keating
showed up in your classroom.

04:21.120 --> 04:22.210
Olivia:
So you've heard of her?

04:22.210 --> 04:23.920
Liv,
it's Annalise Keating.

04:23.920 --> 04:25.920
Annalise Keating
the top defense attorney

04:25.920 --> 04:27.290
and badass professor

04:27.290 --> 04:29.000
from Middleton University
in Philly?

04:29.000 --> 04:30.540
Of course.

04:30.540 --> 04:32.880
I applied to law school there
because of her.

04:32.880 --> 04:36.670
She's a beast.

04:36.670 --> 04:38.290
Google says
she's a criminal.

04:38.290 --> 04:40.670
She's been accused
of some things.

04:40.670 --> 04:42.460
Mm.
But haven't we all.

04:50.000 --> 04:51.880
She wants my help on a case.

04:51.880 --> 04:52.920
Class-action suit.

04:52.920 --> 04:54.960
Defendants are incarcerated
due to over--

04:54.960 --> 04:55.960
Overworked
public defenders.

04:55.960 --> 04:58.170
Yeah, I read about this.

04:58.170 --> 05:00.080
I brought the idea to Fitz,

05:00.080 --> 05:03.040
but we got sidetracked
with another project.

05:03.040 --> 05:04.210
You taking it on?
No.

05:04.210 --> 05:06.830
[ Laughs ]
Are you serious?

05:06.830 --> 05:07.880
Black men going to prison

05:07.880 --> 05:09.250
because their
constitutional rights

05:09.250 --> 05:10.040
have been violated?

05:10.040 --> 05:11.290
Yeah, I'm serious.

05:11.290 --> 05:13.620
Marcus,
I'm not in the game anymore.

05:13.620 --> 05:16.000
Right.

05:16.000 --> 05:17.880
You're a school teacher.

05:17.880 --> 05:19.080
Watch yourself.

05:25.250 --> 05:27.210
I just don't think
I can do it.

05:27.210 --> 05:29.040
Then don't do it.
Do nothing.

05:29.040 --> 05:31.250
Waste your life.
I got to go.

05:31.250 --> 05:33.040
Marcus, why do you --
Why do I return your calls?

05:33.040 --> 05:34.380
Show up for drinks?

05:34.380 --> 05:35.710
Come over
to watch the game?

05:35.710 --> 05:37.040
Yeah.

05:40.250 --> 05:42.330
After everything
that happened,

05:42.330 --> 05:43.960
why are you here?

05:43.960 --> 05:46.670
[ Exhales ]

05:46.670 --> 05:48.330
We're black,

05:48.330 --> 05:50.460
which means
I'll always be here for you,

05:50.460 --> 05:52.000
and I'll always
root for you.

05:54.750 --> 05:56.120
That's how we do.

06:03.580 --> 06:08.500
♪♪

06:08.500 --> 06:10.120
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

06:10.120 --> 06:16.120
♪♪

06:19.120 --> 06:25.120
♪♪

06:28.120 --> 06:34.120
♪♪

06:37.170 --> 06:43.170
♪♪

06:46.210 --> 06:52.210
♪♪

06:55.210 --> 07:01.210
♪♪

07:04.290 --> 07:05.170
[ Knock on door ]

07:05.960 --> 07:07.540
It's a good case.

07:07.540 --> 07:10.620
Your brief is strong,
the injustices are clear.

07:10.620 --> 07:12.080
It's evident these prisoners'
constitutional rights

07:12.080 --> 07:13.500
are being violated.

07:13.500 --> 07:14.790
Some of their stories
are quite moving.

07:14.790 --> 07:16.080
I sense a "but" coming.

07:16.080 --> 07:17.380
But there is one problem.

07:17.380 --> 07:18.210
You.

07:20.460 --> 07:22.580
Annalise Keating
can't be the face of this.

07:22.580 --> 07:23.960
I did a little research.

07:23.960 --> 07:25.830
Murdered husband,
stint in jail...

07:25.830 --> 07:26.830
I was wrongfully accused,

07:26.830 --> 07:28.210
just like
many of my plaintiffs.

07:28.210 --> 07:29.750
Your tenure at Middleton
was nullified.

07:29.750 --> 07:31.380
You were almost disbarred
for alcoholism.

07:31.380 --> 07:32.790
I'm sober now.

07:32.790 --> 07:35.120
Ms. Keating.

07:35.120 --> 07:37.250
You'd be the national press'
featured entrée

07:37.250 --> 07:39.330
for almost a month
of news cycles.

07:39.330 --> 07:41.500
Arson charges for dinner,
murder for dessert.

07:41.500 --> 07:42.920
Even if I was able to spin

07:42.920 --> 07:44.960
this rather colorful
history of yours,

07:44.960 --> 07:46.580
you'd still
have to pull off a miracle

07:46.580 --> 07:48.540
to get the Supreme Court
to come anywhere near this case.

07:48.540 --> 07:49.830
So you're saying
I'm a hot mess.

07:50.790 --> 07:51.830
Yes.

07:54.080 --> 07:56.120
I thought you were able
to move mountains.

07:56.120 --> 07:58.330
That's why I came here
looking for you.

07:58.330 --> 08:01.170
Your reputation was
supposed to speak for itself.

08:08.040 --> 08:09.210
Have a safe trip
back to Philadelphia.

08:21.250 --> 08:27.250
♪♪

08:27.830 --> 08:33.830
♪♪

08:34.710 --> 08:35.620
[ Knock on door ]

08:37.960 --> 08:39.290
If we're gonna
work together,

08:39.290 --> 08:41.000
then there is one thing
you need to understand.

08:41.000 --> 08:42.080
This is my town,
my game, my rules.

08:44.210 --> 08:45.620
Understood?

08:45.620 --> 08:47.080
Understood.

08:47.080 --> 08:52.540
♪♪

08:56.830 --> 08:58.080
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

08:58.080 --> 08:59.540
This isn't
a good idea.
I know.

08:59.540 --> 09:01.250
He doesn't want
to see you.
I know.

09:01.250 --> 09:03.000
I had nothing
to do with this.

09:03.000 --> 09:04.250
We never talked.
I know.

09:11.330 --> 09:13.960
Hi.

09:17.500 --> 09:18.790
How can I help you,
Olivia?

09:22.380 --> 09:23.790
Class-action suit.

09:23.790 --> 09:24.920
100 plaintiffs.

09:24.920 --> 09:26.880
Constitutional rights
are being violated.

09:26.880 --> 09:29.170
I'm familiar.

09:29.170 --> 09:30.880
Why do you need our help?

09:30.880 --> 09:31.880
It's a big case.

09:31.880 --> 09:32.920
A huge fight.

09:32.920 --> 09:34.830
I can't do it alone.

09:37.790 --> 09:40.120
Olivia Pope
asking for help.

09:40.120 --> 09:41.380
That's a first.

09:49.250 --> 09:51.080
I did not come here
for forgiveness.

09:56.170 --> 09:59.710
I know you don't like me.

09:59.710 --> 10:01.460
But I also know

10:01.460 --> 10:03.790
that you want
to change the world,

10:03.790 --> 10:05.210
that it sickens you

10:05.210 --> 10:07.170
that there are people
in this country

10:07.170 --> 10:08.710
who are literally punished

10:08.710 --> 10:11.330
because of disadvantages
they were born into.

10:11.330 --> 10:12.830
That is why you started
this institute --

10:12.830 --> 10:14.120
to give them hope

10:14.120 --> 10:16.000
that their
American nightmare

10:16.000 --> 10:17.540
can become
an American dream.

10:17.540 --> 10:19.500
That's what you've done.

10:19.500 --> 10:21.120
That's why I'm here.

10:21.120 --> 10:24.040
So, yes, Olivia Pope

10:24.040 --> 10:27.710
is asking you, Fitz,
for help.

10:27.710 --> 10:29.420
Okay?

10:29.420 --> 10:33.210
♪♪

10:33.210 --> 10:35.330
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

10:46.290 --> 10:48.120
You got here early.

10:48.120 --> 10:49.500
I'm not early.

10:49.500 --> 10:50.960
[ Laughs ]

10:50.960 --> 10:51.960
Meeting doesn't start
till 9:00.

10:51.960 --> 10:53.040
That's right.

10:53.040 --> 10:54.170
Which makes you early.

10:54.170 --> 10:55.380
I'm not early.

10:55.380 --> 10:56.710
I'm ready.

10:56.710 --> 10:58.790
Good morning.

10:58.790 --> 10:59.670
Marcus: Good morning.

10:59.670 --> 11:01.880
Miss Pope,
it is such an honor.

11:01.880 --> 11:03.670
This is my associate
Michaela Pratt.

11:03.670 --> 11:05.460
I cannot even begin to express
how much this means to me.

11:05.460 --> 11:06.880
[ Hushed voice ]
Except you just did.

11:06.880 --> 11:08.250
It's nice to meet you,
Michaela.

11:08.250 --> 11:10.250
Annalise,
this is Marcus Walker.

11:10.250 --> 11:11.920
Welcome to D.C.,
Ms. Keating.
Thanks for having me.

11:11.920 --> 11:13.290
Morning, everyone.

11:13.290 --> 11:14.500
Mr. President.
Morning, sir.

11:14.500 --> 11:16.250
You must be Annalise.

11:16.250 --> 11:17.750
Yes. Hello, Mr. President.

11:17.750 --> 11:19.290
Call me Fitz.

11:19.290 --> 11:20.380
No, thank you, sir,
Mr. President.

11:20.380 --> 11:21.790
Hi, there. I'm --

11:21.790 --> 11:22.670
[ Mumbling ] 44.

11:22.670 --> 11:24.040
Sorry?

11:24.040 --> 11:26.790
44 --
44th President. 44.

11:26.790 --> 11:28.710
That's me.
Olivia: Mr. President,
before we get started,

11:28.710 --> 11:30.790
we wanted to thank you
for agreeing to help.

11:30.790 --> 11:32.040
This is issue is --

11:32.040 --> 11:34.080
An important one.
I know.

11:34.080 --> 11:36.250
Fortunately, President Grant
thinks so, too.

11:36.250 --> 11:37.620
Michaela:
President Grant?

11:37.620 --> 11:38.750
That'd be the other
President Grant.

11:38.750 --> 11:39.750
She agreed
to meet with us?

11:39.750 --> 11:41.540
She has.
[ Gushes ]

11:41.540 --> 11:43.500
Olivia:
That's fantastic.

11:43.500 --> 11:45.080
Marcus:
If we can get the White House
behind our case,

11:45.080 --> 11:46.420
then the Supreme Court
will add us to their docket,

11:46.420 --> 11:47.420
no question.

11:47.420 --> 11:48.080
Let's get to work.

11:49.830 --> 11:51.710
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

11:51.710 --> 11:52.710
Welcome. Come in.

11:52.710 --> 11:54.290
It's so nice to see
all of you.

11:54.290 --> 11:55.380
Fitz, Marcus.

11:55.380 --> 11:56.750
Marcus:
Madam President.

11:56.750 --> 11:58.380
Ms. Keating,
it's a pleasure to meet you.

11:58.380 --> 11:59.830
Is this your first time
in the White House?

11:59.830 --> 12:01.170
It is.
Thank you for meeting with us.

12:01.170 --> 12:02.460
Thank you for coming.

12:02.460 --> 12:04.580
I'm anxious to hear about
this case of yours.

12:10.460 --> 12:12.750
Mellie: All of these people
are innocent?

12:12.750 --> 12:14.040
Annalise: Who knows.

12:14.040 --> 12:15.460
They were never
given a fair defense

12:15.460 --> 12:16.750
because they couldn't
afford one.

12:16.750 --> 12:18.120
If we're able to get

12:18.120 --> 12:19.330
the Supreme Court
to hear their case,

12:19.330 --> 12:20.670
if we're able to win it,

12:20.670 --> 12:22.710
we can change the system,
and we can do it now.

12:22.710 --> 12:24.420
You and I are in agreement,
Ms. Keating.

12:24.420 --> 12:26.420
The system
does need to change.

12:26.420 --> 12:27.620
[ Inhales deeply ]

12:27.620 --> 12:29.080
But it's not gonna
happen this way.

12:29.080 --> 12:31.080
Madam President,
it's a solid case,

12:31.080 --> 12:32.460
if only the White House

12:32.460 --> 12:34.500
put pressure on the justices
to hear it.

12:34.500 --> 12:36.040
Don't get me wrong.
I like the case.

12:36.040 --> 12:37.290
I just don't like
the court.

12:37.290 --> 12:38.790
You put this case before
the current roster of judges,

12:38.790 --> 12:40.040
you won't win.

12:40.040 --> 12:41.420
David: There are rumblings

12:41.420 --> 12:43.210
that at least a couple of
the more conservative judges

12:43.210 --> 12:44.830
may be considering
retirement.

12:44.830 --> 12:46.080
Marsh,
maybe Kensington.

12:46.080 --> 12:47.290
This time next year,

12:47.290 --> 12:48.460
you could be facing
a whole new ball game.

12:48.460 --> 12:49.620
Next year?

12:49.620 --> 12:50.670
Fitz: We don't even know

12:50.670 --> 12:52.080
whether these judges
are gonna retire.

12:52.080 --> 12:53.380
You're gonna delay
justice for these people

12:53.380 --> 12:54.620
based on a rumor?

12:54.620 --> 12:56.420
Based on certainty.

12:56.420 --> 12:57.960
The certainty that
if we move forward
with this now,

12:57.960 --> 12:59.170
we will be shut down.

12:59.170 --> 13:01.710
And all the work
that you have done

13:01.710 --> 13:03.210
will be for naught.
All the work
I've done?

13:03.210 --> 13:04.500
Let me tell you about
the work that I've done --

13:04.500 --> 13:05.500
Madam President,
may I speak to you privately?

13:05.500 --> 13:07.380
Fitz:
Olivia, let's not --
No. It's okay.

13:07.380 --> 13:08.620
Let's.

13:08.620 --> 13:11.420
Please, uh, everyone,
give us the room.

13:11.420 --> 13:12.620
Mellie:
Ms. Keating, thank you.

13:12.620 --> 13:14.330
I'm so sorry we couldn't
be more accommodating.

13:14.330 --> 13:16.710
Madam President,
thank you for your time.

13:24.000 --> 13:25.040
[ Door closes ]

13:27.120 --> 13:29.040
Why did you agree
to take this meeting

13:29.040 --> 13:30.670
if you knew
you were going to say no?

13:30.670 --> 13:31.670
[ Scoffs ]

13:31.670 --> 13:33.080
First of all,

13:33.080 --> 13:34.500
I agreed to this meeting
as a favor to Fitz.

13:34.500 --> 13:37.080
And secondly,
I didn't say no.

13:37.080 --> 13:39.040
I said not now.

13:39.040 --> 13:40.830
This is not the time
to punish me.

13:42.290 --> 13:43.960
You really think
I'm that small?

13:43.960 --> 13:45.670
I think you're putting
the brakes on

13:45.670 --> 13:47.120
something
you should want.

13:47.120 --> 13:48.250
And there has to be
a reason.

13:48.250 --> 13:50.380
I want this case to move forward
in a year

13:50.380 --> 13:52.580
when it actually has a chance
of succeeding.

13:52.580 --> 13:54.710
The only reason
you want this case
to happen now

13:54.710 --> 13:56.000
is because
you need a win.

13:56.000 --> 13:57.330
You need a win

13:57.330 --> 13:59.330
while there's still
a chance for you

13:59.330 --> 14:01.580
to scrape back some influence
in this town.

14:01.580 --> 14:03.000
Beyond the occasional
teaching gig, that is.

14:03.000 --> 14:05.380
Madam President, I don't --

14:05.380 --> 14:07.040
Go ahead. Tell me I'm wrong.

14:08.790 --> 14:09.880
It wouldn't be the first time
you stood in this room

14:09.880 --> 14:11.040
and lied to my face.

14:13.250 --> 14:15.670
♪♪

14:15.670 --> 14:16.880
We're going
to the Supreme Court

14:16.880 --> 14:18.210
with or without you.

14:18.210 --> 14:20.830
You do that,

14:20.830 --> 14:22.120
you will find yourself

14:22.120 --> 14:24.080
an adversary
of the White House.

14:24.080 --> 14:28.250
♪♪

14:28.250 --> 14:30.000
Wouldn't be the first time
for that, either.

14:30.000 --> 14:36.000
♪♪

14:36.830 --> 14:37.750
[ Door closes ]

14:43.000 --> 14:44.460
Ooh, that was fast.

14:44.460 --> 14:45.540
Did the radiologist say yes
to the payoff,

14:45.540 --> 14:46.920
or are we going to have
to turn the screws a little?

14:46.920 --> 14:48.170
I couldn't tell you.
Sounds juicy, though.

14:48.170 --> 14:49.710
Oh.

14:49.710 --> 14:51.670
Sure is quiet
around here.

14:51.670 --> 14:53.420
Everyone call in sick,
or...?

14:53.420 --> 14:55.460
We're running down cases.

14:55.460 --> 14:57.880
So can I help you, Jake?

14:57.880 --> 15:00.210
Admiral? Command?

15:00.210 --> 15:02.540
What am I supposed to call you
these days anyway?

15:02.540 --> 15:04.000
There's a case
making its way

15:04.000 --> 15:05.330
towards the Supreme Court,
Perkins.

15:05.330 --> 15:06.420
President Grant would prefer

15:06.420 --> 15:07.920
that it stall out
before it gets there.

15:07.920 --> 15:09.420
And?

15:09.420 --> 15:12.460
You're coming to us
when you have B613?

15:13.620 --> 15:14.830
I thought you'd take
a personal interest
in this case.

15:14.830 --> 15:16.290
What's the case?

15:16.290 --> 15:18.250
It's a criminal-justice reform
class-action

15:18.250 --> 15:19.920
championed by none other
than Olivia Pope.

15:19.920 --> 15:21.750
Yeah, well,
that's going to be a big no.

15:21.750 --> 15:23.120
I have no interest

15:23.120 --> 15:25.080
in anything having to do
with Olivia Pope.

15:25.080 --> 15:26.540
Mm.
Your RSS feed begs to differ.

15:26.540 --> 15:28.420
How many articles about Olivia
have you read this month?

15:28.420 --> 15:29.710
20? 30?

15:29.710 --> 15:31.250
[ Chuckles ]

15:31.250 --> 15:33.080
You're spying
on my Internet history?

15:33.080 --> 15:35.170
You and about 300 million
of your fellow citizens.

15:35.170 --> 15:36.420
Look, here's the deal.

15:36.420 --> 15:38.420
If Liv's able to score a win
with this case,

15:38.420 --> 15:39.830
it'll clear a path
for her

15:39.830 --> 15:41.120
right back
into the halls of power.

15:41.120 --> 15:42.710
Are you really
gonna tell me

15:42.710 --> 15:45.120
you're willing to stand by
and let that happen?

15:51.460 --> 15:52.670
The President
refused to help?

15:52.670 --> 15:54.250
President Grant
has made her decision.

15:54.250 --> 15:55.960
Nothing we do now
will change that.

15:55.960 --> 15:57.080
She made that
crystal clear.

15:57.080 --> 15:58.670
That's it?

15:58.670 --> 15:59.670
That's what I get

15:59.670 --> 16:01.750
by having Olivia Pope
on my team --

16:01.750 --> 16:03.120
resignation.

16:03.120 --> 16:04.830
You were supposed to
convince her.

16:04.830 --> 16:06.460
What happened
when we left the room?

16:06.460 --> 16:08.080
It doesn't matter.
It matters to me.

16:09.920 --> 16:11.710
What'd you talk about?

16:11.710 --> 16:13.080
What do you think
we talked about?

16:13.080 --> 16:14.460
We talked about you.

16:16.170 --> 16:17.500
Me?

16:17.500 --> 16:19.330
You think the President
doesn't get a full briefing

16:19.330 --> 16:20.710
on every person
who sets foot in her office,

16:20.710 --> 16:23.120
especially when that person's
got a past like yours?

16:23.120 --> 16:24.580
Annalise,
she'd made up her mind

16:24.580 --> 16:26.170
before you even
opened your mouth.

16:35.120 --> 16:36.290
That woman is impossible!

16:36.290 --> 16:38.250
Fitz: She's passionate
about the case.

16:38.250 --> 16:39.330
And I'm not passionate
about the case?

16:39.330 --> 16:41.250
It's not my fault

16:41.250 --> 16:42.960
Mellie has chosen
to be petty.

16:42.960 --> 16:44.750
It's not Annalise's fault
either.

16:44.750 --> 16:46.040
Maybe I could go back

16:46.040 --> 16:47.500
and try to change
Mellie's mind.

16:47.500 --> 16:48.460
Or maybe
we don't need Mellie.

16:48.460 --> 16:49.830
What?

16:49.830 --> 16:51.880
Cut out the middle man.

16:51.880 --> 16:53.920
Put pressure on
the Supreme Court ourselves.

16:53.920 --> 16:55.330
The Fourteenth Amendment

16:55.330 --> 16:56.710
guarantees equal protection
under the law.

16:56.710 --> 16:58.000
Which is simply impossible

16:58.000 --> 16:59.330
if public defenders

16:59.330 --> 17:01.250
are unable to meet
the same standards

17:01.250 --> 17:03.380
as their privately paid
counterparts.

17:03.380 --> 17:06.330
The Supreme Court must act
to correct that injustice...

17:06.330 --> 17:07.330
You need a majority

17:07.330 --> 17:08.830
to win a case
in The Supreme Court.

17:08.830 --> 17:10.830
But to have it heard
only takes four judges.

17:10.830 --> 17:12.380
Stupid "rule of four."

17:12.380 --> 17:14.380
Justice Gutierrez
has already expressed

17:14.380 --> 17:15.880
his support for Team Liv.

17:15.880 --> 17:17.170
She only needs three more.

17:17.170 --> 17:18.330
Luckily,
Kensington and Marsh

17:18.330 --> 17:19.540
are super
into states' rights.

17:19.540 --> 17:21.120
There's no way
they'd entertain this case.

17:21.120 --> 17:22.540
Which leaves these six.

17:22.540 --> 17:24.120
We get four of them
on our side,

17:24.120 --> 17:25.750
and Annalise Keating
is done.

17:25.750 --> 17:27.170
Woman: Of course
Justice Ribas believes

17:27.170 --> 17:28.420
in the right to counsel,

17:28.420 --> 17:29.830
but the Constitution
doesn't say anything

17:29.830 --> 17:31.540
about the right
to good counsel.

17:31.540 --> 17:33.540
She's a strict
constitutionalist.

17:33.540 --> 17:34.830
You don't say.

17:34.830 --> 17:37.620
Public defenders
are overworked and underpaid,

17:37.620 --> 17:40.580
resulting in an inordinate
amount of plea deals.

17:40.580 --> 17:42.710
Innocent people
are willfully going to jail

17:42.710 --> 17:44.380
simply because
they're poor.

17:44.380 --> 17:45.580
There's no doubt
the system is broken.

17:45.580 --> 17:46.830
But should
the federal government

17:46.830 --> 17:47.830
get involved
in a state program?

17:47.830 --> 17:49.380
Absolutely not.

17:49.380 --> 17:51.420
Which is why we'll rule
to send the case back

17:51.420 --> 17:52.920
to the Pennsylvania
circuit court.

17:52.920 --> 17:54.120
Justice Bass:
I'm sorry, Mr. Walker,

17:54.120 --> 17:55.920
but I have
a more pressing matter

17:55.920 --> 17:58.000
to attend to.
Your Honor,
what could be more pressing

17:58.000 --> 17:59.420
than 90% of defendants

17:59.420 --> 18:00.960
being unable to afford
competent counsel?

18:02.080 --> 18:03.710
Oh.
Excuse me.

18:03.710 --> 18:04.710
♪ In my house ♪

18:04.710 --> 18:05.710
Hold tight.

18:05.710 --> 18:07.170
Justice Bass?

18:07.170 --> 18:08.420
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

18:08.420 --> 18:09.880
Three down. One to go.

18:09.880 --> 18:11.500
So it all rests on --

18:11.500 --> 18:12.830
Quinn:
Justice Mark Spivey.

18:12.830 --> 18:14.710
Of course.
He's always the swing vote.

18:14.710 --> 18:16.500
A wild card.
There's no telling
what he'll do.

18:16.500 --> 18:18.710
And he never reveals
how he's ruling beforehand.

18:18.710 --> 18:20.040
Marcus:
Just got off the phone
with Spivey's law clerk,

18:20.040 --> 18:21.460
and he agrees with you,
Liv.

18:21.460 --> 18:23.500
With a little more media push,
he can be swayed.

18:23.500 --> 18:25.380
Good. Let's set up a sit-down
for me and Noah Baker.

18:25.380 --> 18:26.420
Annalise: I don't think
that's a good idea.

18:26.420 --> 18:28.790
No, you're right.
It should be a woman.

18:28.790 --> 18:30.920
Maybe Francesca Hunter?

18:30.920 --> 18:32.420
No, I mean I don't think
it's a good idea

18:32.420 --> 18:33.620
for you
to do the interview.

18:33.620 --> 18:34.790
I should do it.

18:34.790 --> 18:37.040
You?
Yes.

18:37.040 --> 18:38.250
It's my case.
Put me on camera.

18:38.250 --> 18:40.790
If I do that,
they will tear you apart.

18:40.790 --> 18:42.580
Bring up all your past sins.

18:42.580 --> 18:43.670
Fine. Bring it on.

18:43.670 --> 18:45.080
I'm tired of hiding
in the shadows.

18:45.080 --> 18:47.040
Truth is our greatest weapon.
You said so yourself.

18:47.040 --> 18:48.330
Truth
can be unpredictable.

18:48.330 --> 18:49.460
At this point,
what's most important

18:49.460 --> 18:50.500
is staying on message

18:50.500 --> 18:52.080
and selling this
to Justice Spivey.

18:52.080 --> 18:53.500
Just like you sold it
to President Grant?

18:59.500 --> 19:01.580
Are you questioning
my tactics?

19:01.580 --> 19:02.330
Should I be?

19:04.380 --> 19:05.330
How about you both
do the interview?

19:05.330 --> 19:06.330
Together.

19:08.000 --> 19:09.920
Excuse me?

19:09.920 --> 19:11.290
Annalise, you can convey
the passion behind the case.

19:11.290 --> 19:12.500
Tug at Spivey's heartstrings.

19:12.500 --> 19:13.920
And if the interview
begins to take a turn

19:13.920 --> 19:15.250
towards personal issues,

19:15.250 --> 19:17.540
then Ms. Pope,
you can steer it back

19:17.540 --> 19:19.670
to what's most important --
this case.

19:19.670 --> 19:21.040
Right?

19:21.040 --> 19:22.790
That's exactly
what I was gonna say.

19:30.580 --> 19:32.210
Okay.

19:33.460 --> 19:34.540
Fine.

19:37.080 --> 19:38.500
[ Hushed voice ]
Thank God.

19:38.500 --> 19:40.210
Olivia:
If we do this right,

19:40.210 --> 19:41.540
this interview
could be the push

19:41.540 --> 19:42.960
that Spivey needs
to hear the case.

19:42.960 --> 19:44.290
I'll set it up.
I'll call
Spivey's people

19:44.290 --> 19:46.290
to make sure
he's watching.
Great.

19:52.460 --> 19:56.620
Please tell me you know
a good hairdresser.

19:56.620 --> 19:59.000
[ Chuckles ]

19:59.000 --> 20:00.620
You're telling me
Spivey is clean?

20:00.620 --> 20:02.170
No weird porn searches?

20:02.170 --> 20:03.250
Not even
a creepy library book?

20:03.250 --> 20:04.580
Guy's so clean
it's freaky.

20:04.580 --> 20:05.880
If we can't
hamstring Spivey,

20:05.880 --> 20:06.790
we could be in trouble.

20:06.790 --> 20:08.080
Liv's killing it
in the media.

20:08.080 --> 20:09.290
The public wants reform.

20:09.290 --> 20:10.580
Olivia thinks
she can get away

20:10.580 --> 20:12.330
with ramming it down
the Supreme Court's throat.

20:12.330 --> 20:13.420
I mean, why not, right?

20:13.420 --> 20:15.080
She's gotten away
with everything else.

20:15.080 --> 20:16.670
That's Liv, though.
Nothing ever sticks to her.

20:16.670 --> 20:18.380
There's got to be
dirt on Spivey somewhere.

20:18.380 --> 20:19.790
Maybe he's just
a man of principle.

20:19.790 --> 20:21.830
Or he's smart.
Quinn: Charlie's right.
He is smart.

20:21.830 --> 20:23.880
Smart enough
to store his dirty laundry

20:23.880 --> 20:25.120
on a separate server.

20:25.120 --> 20:25.920
Find it.

20:27.960 --> 20:29.210
Thank you.

20:31.880 --> 20:33.000
[ Hushed voice ]
They haven't found anything

20:33.000 --> 20:34.080
on Justice Spivey?

20:34.080 --> 20:36.000
They're still looking.

20:36.000 --> 20:37.170
[ Exhales ]
They're good.

20:37.170 --> 20:38.330
We'll get
something we can use

20:38.330 --> 20:39.420
to nudge him over
to our side of the fence.

20:39.420 --> 20:41.040
Our side of the fence.
Wonderful.

20:41.040 --> 20:41.830
Yes, ma'am.

20:42.500 --> 20:43.580
What about her?

20:43.580 --> 20:46.830
Her?
She will find a way.

20:46.830 --> 20:48.540
Even if we get Spivey
on our side,

20:48.540 --> 20:50.920
Olivia will find a way
to turn the tide against us.

20:50.920 --> 20:52.170
Again.

20:52.170 --> 20:54.000
It's what she does.
She wins.

20:54.000 --> 20:55.330
Not without the White House
in her corner.

20:55.330 --> 20:57.420
Pay attention.
We are in her corner.

20:57.420 --> 20:59.000
I let her resign.

20:59.000 --> 21:01.000
I let her
keep her dignity.

21:01.000 --> 21:02.080
Everyone still thinks

21:02.080 --> 21:03.330
that Olivia Pope
is Olivia Pope.

21:03.330 --> 21:05.750
Competent, trusted,
right hand of the King.

21:05.750 --> 21:09.420
Because I let her stay
Olivia Pope.

21:09.420 --> 21:11.290
I didn't crush her.

21:11.290 --> 21:13.500
And this is my reward.

21:13.500 --> 21:14.790
[ Laughs ]

21:14.790 --> 21:16.500
No good deed...

21:16.500 --> 21:18.420
You had to help her.

21:18.420 --> 21:20.170
If the public
knew the true circumstances

21:20.170 --> 21:21.920
behind
Olivia Pope's dismissal,

21:21.920 --> 21:23.500
it wouldn't have simply
hurt her.

21:23.500 --> 21:25.710
It would have
hurt us, too.
A flesh wound.

21:25.710 --> 21:27.080
We would have found a way
to deal with it

21:27.080 --> 21:28.580
one way or the other.

21:28.580 --> 21:29.580
At the end of the day,
we would've been fine.

21:29.580 --> 21:31.670
[ Inhales deeply ]

21:31.670 --> 21:33.210
[ Exhales ]

21:35.460 --> 21:37.040
We will be fine.

21:37.920 --> 21:39.000
Ma'am,
if you're suggesting

21:39.000 --> 21:40.210
that we leak
that information now --

21:40.210 --> 21:41.880
Us? The White House?

21:41.880 --> 21:43.120
Leak Liv's firing?

21:43.120 --> 21:45.880
That would be beneath us.

21:45.880 --> 21:48.250
But you are working
with her old team, yes?

21:48.250 --> 21:49.790
I am.

21:49.790 --> 21:51.830
♪♪

21:51.830 --> 21:53.330
Is it beneath them?

21:53.330 --> 21:56.040
♪♪

21:56.040 --> 21:57.540
Yes, Madam President.

21:57.540 --> 22:01.170
♪♪

22:05.670 --> 22:06.790
So she shows up at his house
at 2:00 a.m.

22:06.790 --> 22:08.420
with the other girl
in the back seat?

22:08.420 --> 22:10.040
Yes, girl.
Then, they started fighting.

22:10.040 --> 22:12.000
It was all some straight up
ratchet mess.

22:12.000 --> 22:13.710
That's how your family
do though.

22:13.710 --> 22:15.080
[ Laughs ]
No,
that's just one cousin.

22:15.080 --> 22:16.250
They are not
all like that.

22:16.250 --> 22:17.790
Everybody got
one hood cousin.

22:17.790 --> 22:19.830
Or aunt.
Or uncle
who used to be a pimp.

22:19.830 --> 22:21.710
And then found Jesus.
Oh, I got two of those.

22:21.710 --> 22:26.210
[ Laughter ]

22:30.460 --> 22:32.040
Can you turn that up?

22:35.620 --> 22:37.420
Man:
Sources are saying that

22:37.420 --> 22:39.500
former Chief of Staff
Olivia Pope's interest

22:39.500 --> 22:42.000
in the criminal-justice
class-action suit

22:42.000 --> 22:45.250
is based on a personal vendetta
against President Grant

22:45.250 --> 22:48.040
due to Ms. Pope's being ousted
from the White House.

22:48.040 --> 22:50.170
Audrey Campo:
I can neither confirm
nor deny rumors

22:50.170 --> 22:51.540
that Olivia Pope was fired
from the White House.

22:51.540 --> 22:54.170
But I will say
that President Grant

22:54.170 --> 22:55.710
will not be working
with Ms. Pope

22:55.710 --> 22:57.540
on any recent
or future endeavors.

22:59.460 --> 23:01.210
Annalise: You said
you left on good terms,

23:01.210 --> 23:02.620
that I was the problem
with this case.

23:02.620 --> 23:04.880
But really, it's you.

23:04.880 --> 23:05.880
You lied to me.

23:05.880 --> 23:06.960
Can you give us a minute?

23:14.580 --> 23:16.330
So?

23:16.330 --> 23:17.750
Is it true?

23:17.750 --> 23:19.290
I didn't lie.

23:19.290 --> 23:20.920
My resignation
was complicated.

23:20.920 --> 23:22.460
Sounds like more spin
to me.

23:22.460 --> 23:24.290
You came to me
asking for my help --

23:24.290 --> 23:26.290
Because I thought you had
a bite behind that bark.

23:26.290 --> 23:27.880
But instead I found
a siddity phony

23:27.880 --> 23:29.830
who judged me from the minute
she laid eyes on me.

23:29.830 --> 23:30.830
I never judged you.

23:30.830 --> 23:32.710
Oh,
you judged me immediately.

23:32.710 --> 23:34.670
Just like a white man
in a boardroom

23:34.670 --> 23:35.830
looking down on me

23:35.830 --> 23:38.040
because my hips are too wide
and my hue too dark.

23:38.040 --> 23:39.170
Oh, so we're going there.

23:39.170 --> 23:40.420
Wow.

23:40.420 --> 23:41.790
You think we soul sisters

23:41.790 --> 23:43.290
just 'cause you rented out
a hair salon for a few hours

23:43.290 --> 23:44.250
on the black side of town?

23:44.250 --> 23:45.420
Please.

23:45.420 --> 23:46.620
I've dealt with plenty

23:46.620 --> 23:48.750
of bougie-ass black women
just like you.

23:48.750 --> 23:50.880
Spent most of your life
in boarding school,

23:50.880 --> 23:52.080
Ivy League Universities,

23:52.080 --> 23:53.290
with a horse
between your legs

23:53.290 --> 23:54.880
and a silver spoon
in your mouth.

23:54.880 --> 23:56.500
You're not the only one
who knows how to Google.

23:58.500 --> 24:01.540
You called me a hot mess,
remember?

24:01.540 --> 24:03.920
But it sounds to me

24:03.920 --> 24:06.330
that despite
all of your failed attempts

24:06.330 --> 24:08.920
to stand above me
on your little pedestal,

24:08.920 --> 24:11.790
we're the same.

24:11.790 --> 24:15.380
So keep it real,
Olivia Pope.

24:15.380 --> 24:16.960
Why'd you leave
the White House?

24:20.830 --> 24:23.210
You know, your skin tone
and measurements

24:23.210 --> 24:25.540
aren't the reason
people don't like you.

24:25.540 --> 24:28.290
It's you,
Annalise Keating.

24:28.290 --> 24:32.330
You are a bully
who insults people

24:32.330 --> 24:33.620
and then wonders
why they won't help you.

24:33.620 --> 24:34.880
But hey, you're just
trying to keep it real?

24:34.880 --> 24:36.380
Right?

24:36.380 --> 24:37.960
How's that
working out for you?

24:37.960 --> 24:39.460
Can't be that great

24:39.460 --> 24:41.500
if you had to haul
your broke ass on the Megabus

24:41.500 --> 24:43.500
to beg for my help.

24:43.500 --> 24:45.960
You may think you know who I am
and what I'm about,

24:45.960 --> 24:47.460
but don't get it twisted.

24:47.460 --> 24:49.380
We are not the same.

24:49.380 --> 24:51.330
So allow me
to reintroduce myself.

24:51.330 --> 24:53.170
My name is Olivia Pope.

24:53.170 --> 24:55.920
And I don't have
to explain myself to anyone.

24:55.920 --> 24:57.540
Especially you.

25:05.250 --> 25:06.790
Kevin,
you can come back.

25:06.790 --> 25:08.790
We're done.

25:08.790 --> 25:10.420
Don't worry about
your wash and press.

25:10.420 --> 25:11.540
I'll be sure to put that

25:11.540 --> 25:13.620
on my siddity-ass,
no limit, platinum card.

25:13.620 --> 25:15.250
I'll pay
for my own damn hair.
Okay.

25:21.000 --> 25:22.750
Man: Still no comment
from Olivia Pope

25:22.750 --> 25:24.080
on the allegations

25:24.080 --> 25:25.750
that she was fired
from the White House.

25:25.750 --> 25:28.170
Insiders in Washington
are left speculating

25:28.170 --> 25:29.540
about what could've happened

25:29.540 --> 25:31.080
behind the closed doors
of the Oval,

25:31.080 --> 25:32.670
how Pope became a pariah,

25:32.670 --> 25:33.960
and why she lied about it

25:33.960 --> 25:35.830
in her resignation
announcement.

25:35.830 --> 25:37.670
The White House....
Can you believe this?

25:37.670 --> 25:39.170
The White House
is playing dirty.

25:41.580 --> 25:43.000
It wasn't the White House.

25:43.000 --> 25:44.620
...With more questions
than answers...

25:44.620 --> 25:45.670
This was you?

25:45.670 --> 25:46.790
Well, Quinn technically.

25:46.790 --> 25:48.170
Me by proxy.

25:48.170 --> 25:50.620
Oh. Okay.
So that's a yes.

25:50.620 --> 25:52.880
It wasn't personal.

25:52.880 --> 25:54.040
She needed to be stopped

25:54.040 --> 25:55.250
for the greater good
of our nation.

25:55.250 --> 25:56.380
Stopped?

25:56.380 --> 25:57.790
She's trying to reform
our justice system,

25:57.790 --> 25:59.040
which as Attorney General
of the United Sta--

25:59.040 --> 26:00.420
Mellie wants
the same reform.

26:00.420 --> 26:01.750
Just on a safer timeline.

26:01.750 --> 26:04.920
Sure, but maybe playing it safe
is the problem.

26:04.920 --> 26:06.960
I respect
President Grant's reasoning,

26:06.960 --> 26:08.250
but a "safe timeline"

26:08.250 --> 26:10.330
is not sending someone away
for 20 years

26:10.330 --> 26:12.170
on a simple
possession charge.

26:12.170 --> 26:13.580
But there was a narrative

26:13.580 --> 26:15.460
that is now
being called into question.

26:15.460 --> 26:17.920
Abby...
What?

26:17.920 --> 26:19.620
It's okay to miss her.

26:19.620 --> 26:21.620
...With the White House,
or a calculated move...

26:21.620 --> 26:23.460
I don't miss her.
I just don't trust her.

26:23.460 --> 26:24.460
Okay?

26:24.460 --> 26:25.540
Okay.

26:25.540 --> 26:31.540
♪♪

26:34.540 --> 26:40.540
♪♪

26:43.620 --> 26:49.670
♪♪

26:54.080 --> 26:55.210
Olivia: What is it
that you think

26:55.210 --> 26:55.960
you're gonna
get out of this?

26:58.500 --> 27:00.000
Quinn:
Right now, at the moment,

27:00.000 --> 27:01.620
I'd be happy
just to find my keys.

27:01.620 --> 27:02.790
Oh, would you look
at that.
[ Keys jingle ]

27:02.790 --> 27:04.620
Now, move, please.

27:04.620 --> 27:06.250
You're on the wrong side
of this fight, Quinn.

27:06.250 --> 27:08.080
[ Scoffs ]

27:08.080 --> 27:09.290
I'm on the only side
that matters --

27:09.290 --> 27:10.460
my client's.

27:10.460 --> 27:11.790
Your client?
The White House?

27:11.790 --> 27:13.750
That's who you're working with
to deny the rights

27:13.750 --> 27:16.540
of 90 wrongfully imprisoned
people, right?

27:18.420 --> 27:21.080
I'm not the media, Liv.

27:21.080 --> 27:23.170
You're not going to spin me.

27:23.170 --> 27:25.170
You're not here
because you care
about those people.

27:25.170 --> 27:27.920
You got kicked out of the game
and you want back in.

27:27.920 --> 27:30.040
Don't pretend you
have anything on your
mind other than you.

27:30.040 --> 27:32.620
[ Laughs ] Quinn...

27:32.620 --> 27:33.710
Is that funny?

27:33.710 --> 27:34.750
It's not funny.

27:34.750 --> 27:36.380
It's ironic.

27:36.380 --> 27:38.460
You're not here
for your client.

27:38.460 --> 27:39.830
You're here for me.

27:39.830 --> 27:41.750
You're here for revenge.

27:43.250 --> 27:45.960
And so what if I am?

27:45.960 --> 27:47.790
I'd say I'm more than
a little bit due,

27:47.790 --> 27:49.420
wouldn't you?

27:49.420 --> 27:53.120
You said your QPA
would be about justice.

27:53.120 --> 27:55.750
Don't let go of that.

27:55.750 --> 27:58.290
Don't compromise yourself
just because you hate me.

27:58.290 --> 28:00.620
You're really gonna
want to walk away

28:00.620 --> 28:02.250
before I do something
I regret.

28:02.250 --> 28:03.920
You already have.

28:03.920 --> 28:05.460
You took the case.

28:05.460 --> 28:07.670
I guarantee
one way or the other,

28:07.670 --> 28:09.290
you will come to regret it.

28:09.290 --> 28:15.290
♪♪

28:26.880 --> 28:27.880
You need anything?

28:29.250 --> 28:30.540
What?

28:30.540 --> 28:34.880
Do you need anything
for your interview tomorrow?

28:34.880 --> 28:36.210
No.

28:39.040 --> 28:40.830
You're not gonna
win this thing.

28:44.380 --> 28:46.250
I'll do what I can
with the interview.

28:46.250 --> 28:47.920
But I can only spin
so much.

28:47.920 --> 28:48.670
It won't be enough.

28:50.580 --> 28:53.880
She has problems.

28:53.880 --> 28:55.500
Big problems

28:55.500 --> 28:57.000
that she needs to return
to Philadelphia with

28:57.000 --> 28:57.920
as soon as humanly possible.

28:57.920 --> 28:59.580
That woman --

28:59.580 --> 29:02.040
I think the only one with
big problems here is you.

29:02.040 --> 29:04.580
[ Scoffs ]
Fitz, I'm in no mood.

29:04.580 --> 29:05.750
Neither am I.

29:10.210 --> 29:12.960
You know
how important this is.

29:12.960 --> 29:16.540
You know how long it's taken
for us to get here.

29:16.540 --> 29:19.120
And I am very sorry,
but Annalise Keating --
Oh, for the love --

29:19.120 --> 29:21.080
This is not about
Annalise Keating.

29:21.080 --> 29:24.040
This is about Olivia Pope.

29:24.040 --> 29:26.210
Where the hell is she?

29:27.540 --> 29:29.540
You saw the news.

29:29.540 --> 29:31.290
It's over.

29:31.290 --> 29:33.000
I don't accept that.

29:33.000 --> 29:34.460
You don't accept that.

29:34.460 --> 29:36.500
A couple of reporters
going on TV

29:36.500 --> 29:38.290
saying mean things
about you?

29:38.290 --> 29:39.920
How unique.
How different.

29:39.920 --> 29:41.830
Rare air
you're breathing right now.

29:41.830 --> 29:43.710
Olivia Pope
versus the White House?

29:43.710 --> 29:45.670
That's new.

29:45.670 --> 29:47.790
You forced to work with someone
you can't stand,

29:47.790 --> 29:49.080
someone you disagree with,

29:49.080 --> 29:50.790
someone who calls you
on your crap?

29:50.790 --> 29:54.040
Done it before, Liv,
sailed through it before,

29:54.040 --> 29:55.540
and you never folded.

29:55.540 --> 29:57.540
Not once.

29:57.540 --> 30:00.250
So why now
are you sitting there,

30:00.250 --> 30:02.040
acting like --
Because I'm not
that person anymore.

30:02.040 --> 30:03.620
I'm no longer
the woman you...

30:08.000 --> 30:10.500
Things are different now,
Fitz.

30:10.500 --> 30:11.540
Why did you
take this case?

30:11.540 --> 30:12.790
[ Scoffs ]

30:13.710 --> 30:15.540
Olivia.

30:15.540 --> 30:16.790
Answer the question.

30:16.790 --> 30:17.960
Because it matters.

30:17.960 --> 30:20.170
I took this case
because it matters.

30:20.170 --> 30:21.380
Because you want
to change the world.

30:21.380 --> 30:22.540
Because I want
to change the world.

30:22.540 --> 30:24.710
"Okay"?

30:24.710 --> 30:27.290
Okay.

30:27.290 --> 30:28.710
There you are.

30:28.710 --> 30:34.670
♪♪

30:34.670 --> 30:37.710
You're still you.

30:37.710 --> 30:42.120
They just don't see it.

30:42.120 --> 30:43.380
You just don't see it.

30:43.380 --> 30:49.380
♪♪

30:53.120 --> 30:59.170
♪♪

31:03.000 --> 31:05.290
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

31:09.460 --> 31:10.880
What is that?

31:10.880 --> 31:13.250
Just a little something that
might make you feel better.

31:17.380 --> 31:19.290
Abby!
Abby: What?

31:19.290 --> 31:20.790
Charlie found dirt
on Spivey.

31:20.790 --> 31:23.000
Oh-ho.

31:23.000 --> 31:24.620
Oh, this is good.

31:24.620 --> 31:26.330
There's a reason this guy
kept his secrets buried deep.

31:26.330 --> 31:27.750
The White House
will control Spivey

31:27.750 --> 31:28.880
with that information.

31:28.880 --> 31:30.120
Liv is never gonna know
what hit her.

31:30.120 --> 31:31.170
She is done.

31:31.170 --> 31:33.750
[ Exhales sharply ]

31:37.290 --> 31:38.710
What?

31:38.710 --> 31:39.960
Abby:
I don't know. It's just --

31:39.960 --> 31:41.120
I'm all for playing dirty.

31:41.120 --> 31:42.580
But we're gladiators,
right?

31:42.580 --> 31:44.500
When we play dirty,
it's for a good reason.

31:44.500 --> 31:46.170
This is a good reason.

31:46.170 --> 31:47.620
Of course it is.

31:51.620 --> 31:52.580
Right.

31:57.620 --> 31:58.580
[ Door closes ]

31:58.580 --> 32:01.000
♪♪

32:01.000 --> 32:02.170
Quinn:
I think you'll be happy

32:02.170 --> 32:03.170
with what we found
on Justice Spivey.

32:03.170 --> 32:05.500
Pretty much
speaks for itself.

32:05.500 --> 32:07.080
This is good stuff,
Perkins.

32:07.080 --> 32:08.830
I knew
you'd come through.
Hey.

32:08.830 --> 32:10.330
You never told me --

32:10.330 --> 32:12.170
why's the President
so against a case like this

32:12.170 --> 32:13.670
getting
to the Supreme Court?

32:13.670 --> 32:15.580
You thought
this was about the case?

32:15.580 --> 32:18.420
No, I...

32:18.420 --> 32:20.580
We got the chance
to finally check
Olivia Pope.

32:20.580 --> 32:22.120
It's what we all wanted,
isn't it?

32:22.120 --> 32:23.710
Yeah.

32:23.710 --> 32:25.080
Of course.

32:25.080 --> 32:27.580
You have a good day,
Perkins.

32:27.580 --> 32:32.710
♪♪

32:32.710 --> 32:38.710
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:39.500 --> 32:45.500
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:46.500 --> 32:48.380
[ Whispering ]
You sure this is a good idea?

32:48.380 --> 32:50.460
[ Whispering ]
Not really.

32:50.460 --> 32:53.040
Ms. Pope and Ms. Keating,
thank you for joining us.

32:53.040 --> 32:55.460
Now, before we get
into this case,

32:55.460 --> 32:57.710
there's a new story
we can't ignore

32:57.710 --> 32:59.580
and we'd very much like
to get your response to,

32:59.580 --> 33:00.620
Ms. Pope.

33:00.620 --> 33:02.460
Were you fired
by President Grant?

33:03.500 --> 33:05.000
Yes. I was.

33:05.000 --> 33:08.380
Why were you fired?

33:08.380 --> 33:11.120
Difficult challenges
mean difficult decisions,

33:11.120 --> 33:13.580
having to choose between
the bad or the worse.

33:13.580 --> 33:15.710
Stakes are high.
Inevitably someone gets hurt.

33:15.710 --> 33:17.750
That time it was me.

33:17.750 --> 33:19.920
Do you regret
how you handled anything,

33:19.920 --> 33:22.250
specifically while you were
in the White House?

33:22.250 --> 33:25.040
I regret

33:25.040 --> 33:26.790
that my relationship
with President Grant

33:26.790 --> 33:29.170
dissolved to the point
of my dismissal,

33:29.170 --> 33:31.830
that ties were severed

33:31.830 --> 33:33.710
between the people
I am closest with.

33:33.710 --> 33:36.920
People I have served.
People I have mentored.

33:36.920 --> 33:39.460
People I still love.

33:39.460 --> 33:41.460
But I am a fighter.

33:41.460 --> 33:43.120
So I don't
regret the fight.

33:43.120 --> 33:45.000
I can't.
It's who I am.

33:45.000 --> 33:46.380
It's what I do.

33:46.380 --> 33:50.580
And luckily,
I am not alone.

33:50.580 --> 33:53.880
Next to me is one of
the most courageous fighters

33:53.880 --> 33:54.920
I have ever met.

33:54.920 --> 33:56.500
I am just as proud
to be in the service

33:56.500 --> 33:58.120
of her fight
to get this case heard

33:58.120 --> 33:59.880
by the highest court
of the land

33:59.880 --> 34:02.040
as anything
I have ever done.

34:02.040 --> 34:04.750
And while I understand
the interest in me,

34:04.750 --> 34:06.040
I have lost very little

34:06.040 --> 34:07.080
compared
to the men and women --

34:07.080 --> 34:08.250
many of them innocent --

34:08.250 --> 34:10.420
stuck in prison
for decades

34:10.420 --> 34:12.920
because of
an inadequate defense

34:12.920 --> 34:14.580
provided
by our legal system.

34:14.580 --> 34:16.170
So I respectfully
ask the public,

34:16.170 --> 34:17.580
including you,
Francesca,

34:17.580 --> 34:19.290
to shift focus
to what matters --

34:19.290 --> 34:21.250
the fight to reform
our criminal-justice system.

34:21.250 --> 34:23.330
And the woman
who is leading that charge,

34:23.330 --> 34:24.920
fighting that fight
for all of us.

34:24.920 --> 34:26.330
Annalise Keating.

34:26.330 --> 34:29.920
♪♪

34:29.920 --> 34:31.380
All right then.

34:31.380 --> 34:33.460
Annalise?

34:33.460 --> 34:35.790
Now is the time.

34:35.790 --> 34:38.250
We can't wait
another political season,

34:38.250 --> 34:39.460
another month,
another day.

34:39.460 --> 34:42.000
There are people
rotting in prison

34:42.000 --> 34:44.880
because of a judicial system
that's messed up.

34:44.880 --> 34:46.290
All we're asking

34:46.290 --> 34:48.080
is for an hour
of the court's time

34:48.080 --> 34:50.670
to hear our case,
make a decision.

34:50.670 --> 34:53.670
Help us do that.
Please.

34:53.670 --> 34:58.330
♪♪

34:58.330 --> 35:00.170
Carol: I think what
Ms. Pope and Ms. Keating

35:00.170 --> 35:01.790
said about the current state
of our justice system

35:01.790 --> 35:03.420
was exactly right, Mike.

35:03.420 --> 35:05.080
It is a travesty --
plain and simple.

35:05.080 --> 35:07.580
And if the Supreme Court
doesn't hear this case,

35:07.580 --> 35:08.920
it'd be a damn shame.

35:08.920 --> 35:11.080
Damn right.
Hopefully
Justice Spivey agrees.

35:11.080 --> 35:12.710
Mm-hmm.
Oh, no thank you.

35:12.710 --> 35:14.040
Oh, I-I...

35:14.040 --> 35:15.880
Right.

35:15.880 --> 35:17.620
I didn't mean to --
It's fine.
Don't let me stop you.

35:17.620 --> 35:19.620
[ Chuckles ]

35:19.620 --> 35:21.500
Popcorn and wine
together?

35:21.500 --> 35:23.250
Yeah,
it's kind of my thing.

35:23.250 --> 35:25.920
Looks like a Megabus special
if you ask me.

35:25.920 --> 35:28.420
Mm.
More like a siddity snack.

35:28.420 --> 35:31.620
[ Both laugh ]

35:31.620 --> 35:33.620
[ Phone ringing ]

35:33.620 --> 35:34.960
Marcus.

35:34.960 --> 35:37.750
[ Phone rings ]

35:37.750 --> 35:40.080
Any update on Spivey?

35:40.080 --> 35:41.290
Yeah, he saw the interview.

35:41.290 --> 35:42.670
It didn't change his mind.

35:42.670 --> 35:43.670
He won't hear the case.

35:43.670 --> 35:45.080
[ Exhales ]

35:45.080 --> 35:46.120
Thanks.

35:51.880 --> 35:54.790
I'm sorry.

35:54.790 --> 35:56.420
We have a very conservative
bench right now...

35:56.420 --> 35:59.580
After all of that,
to be so close and still...

36:04.580 --> 36:06.290
I'm sorry.

36:06.290 --> 36:07.420
Mike: They only need
four justices

36:07.420 --> 36:08.620
to get the case heard.
Right.

36:08.620 --> 36:09.960
It's the rule of four.

36:09.960 --> 36:11.170
So Bass and Gutierrez --

36:11.170 --> 36:11.830
they'll vote for this
in a heartbeat.

36:16.210 --> 36:17.380
Michaela:
I wanted to be President.

36:17.380 --> 36:18.580
Growing up,
it's all I thought about.

36:18.580 --> 36:20.000
Or at least a senator.

36:20.000 --> 36:21.750
I had this vision of D.C.

36:21.750 --> 36:23.920
as a place full of
attractive young people,

36:23.920 --> 36:25.000
going to fancy galas,

36:25.000 --> 36:26.750
and trying to do good
in the world.

36:26.750 --> 36:29.250
Instead,
it's like an uglier Philly

36:29.250 --> 36:32.330
with a bunch of narcissistic,
power-hungry cowards.

36:32.330 --> 36:34.290
Hey now --
who you calling ugly?

36:34.290 --> 36:36.080
[ Both laugh ]

36:36.080 --> 36:38.080
Well,
I didn't say everyone.

36:38.080 --> 36:44.080
[ Mid-tempo music plays
over radio ]

36:47.330 --> 36:48.500
Damn.

36:48.500 --> 36:50.250
Strong? [ Chuckles ]

36:50.250 --> 36:52.210
That's why I've been coming here
since I was 16.

36:52.210 --> 36:54.250
You're from here?

36:54.250 --> 36:56.170
This is
the neighborhood.

36:56.170 --> 36:57.750
Good for you
for getting out.

36:57.750 --> 37:00.960
[ Music continues ]

37:00.960 --> 37:03.830
You know, I may live and work
in the other D.C. now.

37:03.830 --> 37:06.170
But everything I've done,
everything I've worked for,

37:06.170 --> 37:07.960
I've done
because of this place --

37:07.960 --> 37:09.960
Because I grew up around

37:09.960 --> 37:11.670
the hardest-working people
in America,

37:11.670 --> 37:12.920
who got the worst treatment,

37:12.920 --> 37:15.000
and I want to do something
to change that.

37:15.000 --> 37:16.750
I'll never stop
working for them.

37:16.750 --> 37:19.580
Just like you'll never stop
fighting for your case

37:19.580 --> 37:20.500
in whatever way you can.

37:21.620 --> 37:23.880
This place has my heart.

37:23.880 --> 37:26.670
Unless it takes my liver.

37:26.670 --> 37:32.120
[ Music continues ]

37:32.120 --> 37:33.920
Anyway,
we had a crap day.

37:33.920 --> 37:35.540
Sorry for making you come
to a place like this.

37:35.540 --> 37:39.710
No.
I'm liking this bar.

37:44.750 --> 37:46.750
[ Phone ringing ]

37:46.750 --> 37:48.380
Asher.

37:48.380 --> 37:50.790
Cool name.

37:50.790 --> 37:53.170
I...I should get going.

37:53.170 --> 37:55.750
Uh, we're -- we're probably
heading home tomorrow,

37:55.750 --> 37:58.670
and, so, I need to pack.

37:58.670 --> 38:01.790
Um...

38:01.790 --> 38:03.330
Thank you for the drink.

38:03.330 --> 38:09.290
[ Music continues ]

38:15.710 --> 38:16.960
[ Knock on door ]

38:29.420 --> 38:30.830
[ Sighs ]

38:30.830 --> 38:32.120
Spivey's decision
wasn't based

38:32.120 --> 38:33.250
on the merits
of the case.

38:36.170 --> 38:38.620
Charlie found it.

38:38.620 --> 38:39.830
I gave it to Jake.
I'm sure he used it.

38:39.830 --> 38:41.500
He must have.

38:41.500 --> 38:43.120
There's no way Spivey saw
that interview last night

38:43.120 --> 38:44.380
without being
affected by it.

38:44.380 --> 38:45.540
If you could find a way

38:45.540 --> 38:47.170
to make
that story disappear,

38:47.170 --> 38:49.170
maybe you'd get
a different result.

38:49.170 --> 38:53.710
To be clear,
I did not do this for you.

38:53.710 --> 38:56.330
You were right.

38:56.330 --> 38:59.830
I did say my QPA
would be about justice.

38:59.830 --> 39:01.120
Now, it still is.

39:06.880 --> 39:09.040
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

39:09.040 --> 39:11.040
[ Knock on door ]

39:11.040 --> 39:11.960
Olivia: Justice Spivey?

39:11.960 --> 39:13.500
Ms. Pope.

39:13.500 --> 39:14.920
Now,
should I tell you up front

39:14.920 --> 39:16.500
that your visit
is futile,

39:16.500 --> 39:18.580
or would you like me
to pretend for a while?

39:18.580 --> 39:20.210
I don't want you
to pretend.

39:20.210 --> 39:22.170
I do want you
to change your vote.

39:22.170 --> 39:23.290
I can't do that.

39:25.830 --> 39:27.210
Actually, you can now.

39:32.960 --> 39:34.330
Six years ago,

39:34.330 --> 39:35.920
your son killed a woman
in a hit and run.

39:35.920 --> 39:37.250
You paid off
the only witness.

39:39.120 --> 39:40.920
How did you get this?

39:40.920 --> 39:42.460
I got it from the same people

39:42.460 --> 39:44.380
who gave it to the White House
yesterday.

39:44.380 --> 39:46.380
Mere hours
before you made up your mind.

39:46.380 --> 39:48.170
I am guessing
that is not a coincidence.

39:50.710 --> 39:52.000
It was an accident.

39:52.000 --> 39:53.620
He -- he wasn't drinking,
he wasn't texting,

39:53.620 --> 39:55.500
he wasn't...

39:55.500 --> 39:58.210
He was 16.

39:58.210 --> 39:59.960
It was an accident.

39:59.960 --> 40:02.540
You people are using this
to blackmail me?

40:02.540 --> 40:04.620
I'm not trying to blackmail you,
Justice Spivey.

40:04.620 --> 40:06.420
In fact,
I want to tell you something

40:06.420 --> 40:07.880
the White House
forgot to mention.

40:07.880 --> 40:11.960
The witness you paid off
died two years ago.

40:11.960 --> 40:14.920
The payment you made
could still take you down.

40:14.920 --> 40:18.040
But without him around to talk,
it's easy to bury.

40:18.040 --> 40:19.330
I'm good
at that kind of thing.

40:19.330 --> 40:21.620
The best, actually.

40:21.620 --> 40:23.420
I can fix it for you,
make it all go away,

40:23.420 --> 40:25.120
get you out
from under the White House.

40:25.120 --> 40:27.460
I only ask one thing
in return.

40:27.460 --> 40:29.290
That I hear the case,
that I side with you.

40:29.290 --> 40:30.670
No.

40:30.670 --> 40:32.710
That you listen
to your conscience.

40:33.920 --> 40:36.250
Like I said,

40:36.250 --> 40:39.040
I didn't come here
to blackmail you.

40:39.040 --> 40:41.500
I'm done
trying to influence people

40:41.500 --> 40:43.080
with anything
but the truth.

40:43.080 --> 40:45.120
And the truth is,

40:45.120 --> 40:47.920
if your son had stood trial
for his crime,

40:47.920 --> 40:50.330
I know that
you would have wanted him

40:50.330 --> 40:54.120
to have the best representation
possible.

40:54.120 --> 40:56.000
The families
of our plaintiffs

40:56.000 --> 40:57.880
want the same thing
for them, too.

40:57.880 --> 40:59.960
Don't they
at least deserve the chance

40:59.960 --> 41:01.710
to have this case heard?

41:01.710 --> 41:04.120
♪♪

41:04.120 --> 41:05.380
Julia:
Reports this afternoon

41:05.380 --> 41:07.170
coming out of
the Supreme Court...

41:07.170 --> 41:09.210
The class-action lawsuit
spearheaded

41:09.210 --> 41:11.880
by former White House
Chief of Staff Olivia Pope,

41:11.880 --> 41:14.290
along with Philadelphia
attorney Annalise Keating,

41:14.290 --> 41:16.540
has just been added
to the court's docket.

41:16.540 --> 41:18.880
Justice Spivey
apparently making

41:18.880 --> 41:21.460
an impassioned plea
to his fellow justices,

41:21.460 --> 41:23.790
asking that they not only
consider the case,

41:23.790 --> 41:25.210
but fast-track it as well.

41:25.210 --> 41:26.620
The stunning decision

41:26.620 --> 41:28.250
is not only a victory
for Pope and Keating,

41:28.250 --> 41:29.790
but is also being hailed

41:29.790 --> 41:31.830
as a significant step forward
in the effort

41:31.830 --> 41:34.670
to reform America's
criminal-justice system.

41:34.670 --> 41:37.170
♪♪

41:37.170 --> 41:38.500
Olivia.

41:38.500 --> 41:39.790
Annalise.

41:39.790 --> 41:42.960
I guess this makes you
exactly what I thought.

41:42.960 --> 41:44.000
What would that be?

41:44.000 --> 41:45.330
A miracle worker.

41:45.330 --> 41:47.210
[ Laughs ]

41:47.210 --> 41:49.080
[ Sighs ]

41:49.080 --> 41:51.170
So what now?

41:51.170 --> 41:52.750
You go on
to your teaching gig?

41:52.750 --> 41:54.250
I go on
to the Supreme Court?

41:54.250 --> 41:56.380
Is that what
you would like to happen?

41:56.380 --> 41:58.500
Not exactly.

41:58.500 --> 42:01.170
You?
Nope.

42:01.170 --> 42:03.080
♪♪

42:03.080 --> 42:05.000
Is this your way of saying
you'll join me?

42:05.000 --> 42:07.460
♪♪

42:07.460 --> 42:09.670
Is this your way
of asking?

42:09.670 --> 42:12.790
♪♪

42:12.790 --> 42:14.290
Let's go.

42:14.290 --> 42:20.290
♪♪

42:23.120 --> 42:25.960
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

